{
  "stem": "95.2",
  "chunk_idx": 15,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There was only 150 people who could stay there to work in a shoe factory.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The others, they were selected once a week by a Gestapo agent.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "The Gestapo agent would come.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We would stand at roll-call, and he will just point his finger, and you-- and these people would be sent to the concentration camps, or extermination camps.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And only an elite people-- 150 people-- would stay in that camp to work in a shoe factory.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And when we arrived there, the first thing we did is being shaved from head to toe, taking a shower.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Now, we were not given striped uniforms, even though it was a-- a slave labor camp, and a satellite of Auschwitz, but it was not a real concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we were given ill-fitted uniforms.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I mean, clothes that didn't belong to us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I mean right now, ill-fitted uniforms would be perfect because that's what we wear-- ill-fitted suits.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But at that-- at that time it wasn't.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And what happened is they had-- they had the Star of David cut out of the-- of those clothes, on the front of our coat, on the back of our coat, and on both the legs of our trousers, so we can be-- and we were shaved.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We were not given numbers yet.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "That was September 1942.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And speeches-- I mean the Judenaltester, who was the commandant, the Jewish commandant of the camp, OSS [INAUDIBLE] for the Nazis, for the soldiers, telling us what's going to happen with our lives, that there's no more liberty.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We're going to work very hard.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "We're going to eat very little, and you better obey.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "That's it.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And the Kapos-- Kapos were lieutenants.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Most certainly-- now, that first camp, which was a small camp, they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
